    excerptEn: `The washbasin is the heart of the bathroom and one of the most important aesthetic elements in modern interior design. In recent years, the importance of the washbasin in decor has grown dramatically, with a wide range of modern stone, glass, and resin sinks entering the market. This guide covers all washbasin types along with practical buying advice.`,
    excerptFa: `روشویی قلب سرویس بهداشتی و یکی از جنبه‌های مهم زیبایی‌شناختی طراحی دکوراسیون داخلی است. به‌خصوص در سال‌های اخیر اهمیت روشویی در طراحی دکوراسیون مدرن به‌شدت مطرح بوده و شاهد ورود انواع روشویی مدرن و...`,
    image: '/images/articles/modern-washbasin-guide.jpg',
    readTime: 6,
    publishedAt: '2023-02-26',
    bodyEn: [
      `The washbasin is the heart of the bathroom and one of the most important aesthetic aspects of interior design. In recent years, the importance of the washbasin in modern decorating has been strongly emphasized, and we have witnessed the arrival of many attractive and modern washbasins on the market — interesting and beautiful sinks made of stone, glass, and more that we admire but know little about. In this article we intend to discuss these washbasins and their importance in modern interior design.`,
      `Before familiarizing ourselves with the types of modern washbasins available in the Iranian and international markets, it is worth understanding what the best washbasin material is and which options to consider. The most popular option in modern washbasins is ceramic, which is available in various shapes and is easy to clean. This widespread popularity has made it available at different price points to suit every budget. The next option is glass, which despite its high tendency to show water stains, is extremely popular and many people accept its demanding maintenance conditions because of its beautiful appearance. One of the incredibly popular choices in modern design is the resin washbasin, which showcases the style and color of the bathroom.`,
      `Above-counter basins, also known as vessel sinks, are used in contemporary design as an exceptionally beautiful minimalist element. These sinks sit on top of a bathroom shelf or cabinet, and a tall faucet completes their beauty. These sinks are available in a wide variety of shapes, sizes, finishes, and stunning designs.`,
      `This type of modern washbasin, as you can see in the image, sits on top of the bathroom cabinet and its raised edges on the cabinet surface create an interesting visual appeal. The cabinet space in this type of washbasin is very suitable for storing bathroom accessories and can be found in any design and color you desire. Usually, stone or porcelain bowls are used for the sink of these models, and PVC is a suitable material for the cabinet — a material that is completely resistant to the constant moisture of this space.`,
      `As its name suggests, this beautiful sink is installed under the surface of a marble or granite cabinet, and the rim of the basin sits lower than the stone surface, resulting in a seamless look that makes the bathroom cabinet appear more spacious. The undermount washbasin is one of the most popular models of luxury and modern washbasins.`,
      `One of the most popular types of modern luxury washbasins is the vessel basin, which comes in a wide variety of stone, metal, and wood types in diverse dimensions and has many fans. This washbasin does not require a pedestal and sits on top of the countertop surface. The washbasin in the image above is a beautiful classic steel design placed on a wooden cabinet so that the warmth of the wood neutralizes the coldness of the metal and gives the environment a pleasing beauty.`,
      `The wall-mounted washbasin is installed directly on the bathroom wall and is extremely practical for small spaces, because leaving the floor area empty makes this small room appear more spacious. In this design, the water pipes can be hidden inside the wall. These sink models are height-adjustable and allow the use of the space under the sink. In addition, cleaning them is far easier than pedestal washbasins. Wall-mounted washbasins are also available in porcelain, stone, and cabinet versions.`,
      `The console washbasin is considered a combination of the wall-mounted and pedestal washbasin models, except that it has only two legs and occupies less space than a fully-legged washbasin. Of course, these sinks can be installed with four legs or on a cabinet. Generally speaking, however, it consists of a countertop basin with a wall console and two floor legs. The metal frame of this washbasin is excellent for hanging towels and helps make better use of the available space.`,
      `Most of the washbasins we see in today's modern design are pedestal types that are fixed to the floor and give the space a minimalist appearance. Although most traditional washbasins fall into this category, in recent years various stylish and modern pedestal washbasins have entered the market. Among the advantages of these washbasins we can point to their wide variety and reasonable price compared to other modern washbasins. On the other hand, cleaning them is more difficult and their height is not adjustable.`,
      `If you are looking for a modern and stylish washbasin, we recommend semi-recessed sinks. These sinks are usually made of a stone slab or similar materials and resemble a recessed basin or pool, giving the bathroom an opulent appearance. The wall-mounted faucets of these sinks make cleaning inside and around them easier, and they harmonize easily with other design elements of modern washbasins. This washbasin is also available in a wide range of sizes and shapes.`,
      `These narrow, simple, and modern sinks with minimal design occupy very little space and have a trough for collecting and directing water to the drain pipe. They are among the most beautiful types of modern stone washbasins that you can confidently purchase and install in smaller bathrooms.`,
      `The corner sink, as its name implies, is designed to cover a corner in small bathroom rooms and occupy the least possible space. It is therefore very suitable for small bathrooms with limited floor area. Corner sinks can be obtained in both wall-mounted and floor-standing configurations.`,
    ],
