    bodyEn: [
      `Today's construction industry offers a wide variety of adhesives that can be used to bond slab stone to concrete, glass, wood, tile, and other surfaces. However, not every adhesive can be expected to deliver strong long-term bonding, resistance to pressure and heat, and acceptable flexibility. If you are looking for the best and strongest slab stone adhesive on the market for your construction project, stay with us in this article as we introduce the best options available.`,
      `In recent years we have seen extensive use of stone as an important building material in various sections of residential and commercial projects. The main reason for this volume of use and popularity in the construction industry has been the ease of use and relatively reasonable cost of cementitious mortar. However, in recent years the issue of the weight of cementitious mortar and the extra load it imposes on the building was raised — to the point that structural engineers declared that using building mortar makes structures vulnerable and completely defenseless against earthquakes, settlement, moisture, and temperature changes. The other significant issue is the stone bulging during installation and subsequent cracking and fracturing of large slabs. The solution offered to address this problem was the use of stone adhesive.`,
      `In the building materials market, the variety of adhesives seems endless. Therefore, if you intend to purchase without seeing and knowing the product, your task will naturally be somewhat difficult. First and foremost, you should know that not all adhesives are of good quality and you cannot have similar expectations from all of them. Ask the seller about the following characteristics — these are the qualities of the best slab stone adhesive on the market.`,
      `The first question to ask the seller concerns the bonding strength of the slab stone adhesive. A firm and gripping adhesive must be able to securely hold the stone on the desired surface, with minimal probability of it coming loose under various conditions. The seller can provide you with sufficient information about the adhesive's bonding strength.`,
      `In the best case, the adhesive you purchase can be used on all stone, steel, wood, and other surfaces. However, some adhesives on the market are designed exclusively for bonding slabs to a specific surface only, and it is important to pay attention to this point when purchasing. Some adhesives lose their properties over time due to weather changes and rain and are best used only for interior facades; others are also suitable for outdoor use.`,
      `One of the biggest drawbacks of low-quality adhesives available on the market is the possibility of the stone changing color over time. This is something that instant adhesives (super glues) and even powder adhesives do to stone.`,
      `It may seem a little strange at first, but the flexibility of an adhesive reflects its quality. A good quality adhesive stretches and is completely flexible so that during an earthquake or strong wind, with a small amount of movement and minor displacement, it maintains its strength and does not instantly turn to powder.`,
      `The last question concerns the compressive strength of the slab stone adhesive and its resistance to weather changes. Installing stone in cold and warm seasons can cause stone separation due to mortar contraction or expansion. Therefore, it is best to look for an adhesive when purchasing that has good resistance to weather changes and whose volume does not change. This issue is extremely important in fire conditions within a structure.`,
      `In the Iranian market, polyester, epoxy, and powder adhesives are considered the most popular types of slab stone adhesive, and you can choose one according to your needs.`,
      `One of the most common types of adhesives in the Iranian market is polyester-based slab stone adhesive, which despite its low durability and lack of resistance to temperature changes, is used not only for bonding slab stone but in almost all construction work. The reason is undoubtedly the ease of use and the speed with which this adhesive bonds.`,
      `Epoxy-based adhesives have good physical strength and show good resistance to thermal changes. Therefore, if you are looking for a strong and firm adhesive for installing slab panels on the interior or exterior facade of a construction project, standard epoxy adhesive, thermal epoxy adhesive, and UV epoxy adhesive are the best options available.`,
      `Powder adhesive — or what is commonly called tile adhesive — is produced from cement, powder resins, and polymers and requires mixing with water before use to achieve its adhesive properties. Among the positive characteristics of these adhesives are their flexibility and relatively good adhesion, and the fact that after drying they are resistant to moisture.`,
    ],
